    "body": "The main aim here is that the functions no longer take a `code` argument. The code argument was always a bit awkward I think (although the disadvantage of the updated approach is that working out whether to make the funcstate is \"needs_refnanny\" is a little more awkward).\r\n\r\nThe longer-term motivation here is to replace some uses of `INCREF` with `NEWREF`. This is mainly for freethreading-related reasons (because we typically do `INCREF` after assignment which is a little more awkward to make thread-safe). However, `NEWREF` is typically a code fragment rather than a complete line, so it fits better into this scheme than the current one.",
    "closed_at": null,
