                    "name": "da-woods"
                },
                "message": "Refactor of refcounting functions in PyrexTypes\n\nThe main aim here is that the functions no longer take a\n`code` argument. The code argument was always a bit awkward\nI think (although the disadvantage of the updated approach\nis that working out whether to make the funcstate is\n\"needs_refnanny\" is a little more awkward).\n\nThe longer-term motivation here is to replace some uses of\n`INCREF` with `NEWREF`. This is mainly for freethreading-related\nreasons (because we typically do `INCREF` after assignment\nwhich is a little more awkward to make thread-safe).\nHowever, `NEWREF` is typically a code fragment rather than\na complete line, so it fits better into this scheme than the\ncurrent one.",
